<P>Try a human in the same zones. You won't be able to see a tree that you just walked into, or know you're in the water without sound effects(its really damn dark). The last few days some changes were made. I find the troll swamp great now, ogre land is still a bit dark but no worse than Greater Feydark or Toxulia. If you aren't noticing trolls and ogres seeing better now, and especially better than human types, then you may want to check into your video card settings, drivers, or something.

<P>Yes I do agree its a very long run from home to find a human or halfing settlements to raid. The the reverse is true as well, you'll be fairly safe from raids from others, at least safer than the Dark Elves for a while.
<P>&gt; I don't want to be isolated and on a strictly rping point (
<BR>&gt; which is basically what yur post is about) we would be launching
<BR>&gt; constant attacks on the good races but can't do that because we
<BR>&gt; get so absolutely sick of standing in a pitch dark zone ( we
<BR>&gt; live in caves and dark swamps but dont have infravision?!?!?!
<BR>&gt; wtf is that?) wonderin around hoping to have an encounter or
<BR>&gt; sitting in freont of a lizzy camp hour after hour. You dont
<BR>&gt; sound like you have even played an ogre or troll so dont post
<BR>&gt; and dont say uve been a troll or ogre because you wouldnt have
